text: Garden of Eden Station, also known as Pickel's Station and McBride's Station, is a historic gas station located near Warrensburg, Johnson County, Missouri. It was built about 1928, and is a small, relatively unaltered rural gas station constructed of coursed sandstone blocks. (includes 10 photographs from 1993) It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1995. ==References== Category:Gas stations on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Commercial buildings completed in 1928 Category:Buildings and structures in Johnson County, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Johnson County, Missouri
